 replies that she heard man, woman and gunshots. <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Pistorius&amp;src=hash\">#Pistorius</a></p>&mdash; David Smith (@SmithInAfrica) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440765514294362112\">March 4, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-53158dd7e4b0da1677ed2cc3\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-03-04T08:26:34.134Z\">8.26am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440764391927971840\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Roux: &quot;You have watched Sky News, you watched other news channels, you have a retrospective knowledge&quot; and you come to court with that.</p>&mdash; David Smith (@SmithInAfrica) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440764391927971840\">March 4, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440764736192270337\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Roux: On that fateful morning you did not know you were a neighbour of Oscar <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Pistorius&amp;src=hash\">#Pistorius</a>. &quot;You did not even know it was his house.&quot;</p>&mdash; David Smith (@SmithInAfrica) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440764736192270337\">March 4, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-53158d51e4b0da1677ed2cc2\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-03-04T08:24:33.381Z\">8.24am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Burger is being asked by Roux to explain why she thought there was an intruder in Pistorius’s house that night. Roux is suggesting she is using knowledge gleaned from media coverage after the event as part of her testimony. She denies it. “I did not change or alter [it].”<br></p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440763984010936320\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Burger: &quot;I wasn&#39;t in the house... What I heard at that stage, I thought there was an intruder.&quot; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Pistorius&amp;src=hash\">#Pistorius</a></p>&mdash; David Smith (@SmithInAfrica) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440763984010936320\">March 4, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-53158d19e4b0984a90a9e0ba\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-03-04T08:21:48.614Z\">8.21am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440763748626620416\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Burger: &quot;From what I heard I assume there had to be someone threatening their lives. The life-threatening screams she gave were petrified.&quot;</p>&mdash; David Smith (@SmithInAfrica) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440763748626620416\">March 4, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-53158c8be4b0da1677ed2cc1\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-03-04T08:19:35.534Z\">8.19am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Roux has resumed his cross-examination.<br></p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-53158c18e4b0da1677ed2cbf\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-03-04T08:18:19.802Z\">8.18am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The judge has now warned the media to be careful and to heed the orders in place.<br></p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440762432860860416\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Masipa: &quot;I must say this is very disturbing. I must warn the media that you are not going to be treated with soft gloves.&quot; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Pistorius&amp;src=hash\">#Pistorius</a></p>&mdash; David Smith (@SmithInAfrica) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440762432860860416\">March 4, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440762627371696128\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Masipa: No photographs of any witnesses from any source. An investigation will follow. &quot;We will proceed without any further delay.&quot;</p>&mdash; David Smith (@SmithInAfrica) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440762627371696128\">March 4, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-53158bf0e4b0da1677ed2cbd\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-03-04T08:17:16.692Z\">8.17am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Gerrie Nel has called for an investigation into how the picture came to be used.<br></p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440762181571731456\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Nel: Showing photo of witness Michelle Burger on eNCA is &quot;clear violation&quot; of court order and &quot;an investigation should follow&quot;. <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Pistorius&amp;src=hash\">#Pistorius</a></p>&mdash; David Smith (@SmithInAfrica) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440762181571731456\">March 4, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-53158ab2e4b0984a90a9e0b8\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-03-04T08:16:20.894Z\">8.16am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>eNCA, the news channel broadcasting the trial, has denied breaching the order by showing footage of a witness. According to its Twitter account, it has used a still picture of Burger from the website of the university where she works.<br></p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/eNCAnews/statuses/440758620259909632\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>NOTE: &#39;We have not shown any footage of Michelle Burger in court...&#39; - Patrick Conroy, Head of News, eNCA</p>&mdash; eNCA (@eNCAnews) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/eNCAnews/statuses/440758620259909632\">March 4, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/eNCAnews/statuses/440758727571177472\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>NOTE: &#39;We used a still picture from the University website - also carried in daily newspapers.&#39; - Patrick Conroy, Head of News, eNCA</p>&mdash; eNCA (@eNCAnews) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/eNCAnews/statuses/440758727571177472\">March 4, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-5315893ae4b0da1677ed2cb9\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-03-04T08:05:17.653Z\">8.05am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440759464132481024\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Pistorius&amp;src=hash\">#Pistorius</a> looking calm again. Just received a note from his family, nodded and winked. Now stifling a yawn.</p>&mdash; David Smith (@SmithInAfrica) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440759464132481024\">March 4, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-53158697e4b0da1677ed2cb6\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-03-04T07:55:30.471Z\">7.55am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The trial has been adjourned as the prosecutor has just informed the judge that an order prohibiting the broadcast of a witness’s face appears to have been broken. (As you can see from the top of the blog, proceedings are being broadcast live.)<br></p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440756893548441600\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Pistorius&amp;src=hash\">#Pistorius</a> prosecutor Gerrie Nel: &quot;I&#39;ve just been informed they&#39;re showing the witness&#39;s face on TV.&quot; There&#39;s an order against. Adjourned.</p>&mdash; David Smith (@SmithInAfrica) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440756893548441600\">March 4, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-531585e8e4b0da1677ed2cb4\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-03-04T07:51:05.533Z\">7.51am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440757802873540608\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Burger: &quot;Moments before gunshots were fired I heard a woman scream... Her life was threatened severely in the house.&quot; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Pistorius&amp;src=hash\">#Pistorius</a></p>&mdash; David Smith (@SmithInAfrica) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440757802873540608\">March 4, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2014-03-04T07:57:48.001Z\">at 7.57am GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-531585d9e4b0984a90a9e0b3\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-03-04T07:50:50.235Z\">7.50am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440757578574729216\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Masipa warns Burger to answer yes, no, don&#39;t know or don&#39;t remember, or she could be &quot;in the witness box for another day&quot;. <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Pistorius&amp;src=hash\">#Pistorius</a></p>&mdash; David Smith (@SmithInAfrica) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440757578574729216\">March 4, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2014-03-04T07:57:18.110Z\">at 7.57am GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-53158539e4b0da1677ed2cb3\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-03-04T07:50:31.285Z\">7.50am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Pistorius’s counsel, Barry Roux, is continuing his cross-examination of Michelle Burger, who lived 177m from the athlete’s house, and who told the court yesterday that she heard a woman’s “bloodcurdling” screams and “petrified shouts”, followed by four shots on the night Steenkamp died.<br></p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440757249179283456\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Barry Roux pressing witness Michelle Burger on whether <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Pistorius&amp;src=hash\">#Pistorius</a>&#39;s bail application statement on screams made her think: &quot;It cannot be.&quot;</p>&mdash; David Smith (@SmithInAfrica) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440757249179283456\">March 4, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2014-03-04T07:56:41.418Z\">at 7.56am GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-5315833ce4b0da1677ed2cb2\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-03-04T07:39:44.526Z\">7.39am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440753244688482304\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Judge Masipa enters court: &quot;You may be seated, Mr <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Pistorius&amp;src=hash\">#Pistorius</a>.&quot; <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Pistorius&amp;src=hash\">#Pistorius</a> family in public gallery but no sign of mother June Steenkamp.</p>&mdash; David Smith (@SmithInAfrica) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440753244688482304\">March 4, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-531580a1e4b0da1677ed2cb1\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-03-04T07:33:55.265Z\">7.33am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>There’s some fascinating social context in Margie Orford’s piece over on the Guardian Africa Network <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/mar/04/oscar-pistorius-trial-black-stranger-defence\">here</a>. In it, the journalist and author probes the “paranoid imaginings of suburban South Africa”. Here’s a bit of it:<br></p><blockquote class=\"quoted\"><p>The <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/mar/03/oscar-pistorius-michelle-burger-paralympian-reeva-steenkamp-murder-trial\">murder trial of Oscar Pistorius</a> is gearing up to be a John Grisham-style courtroom drama. It will be a battle of ‘expert’ opinions because the uncontested fact is that on Valentine’s Day last year Pistorius fired four shots at close range through a locked bathroom door and killed Reeva Steenkamp. This is not in dispute.</p><p>What is in dispute is his claim that he did not intend to kill his girlfriend. He says he was shooting at somebody else; that he thought there was an ‘intruder’ in the bathroom; that this killing was a mistake; that it was not just another South African femicide.</p><p>So the trial will revolve around Pistorius’ intention: essentially, the psychology of a man who claims to have been driven by fear to shoot before asking any questions. This claim inserts a third body into an all too familiar narrative of domestic violence. This imaginary body of the paranoid imaginings of suburban South Africa has lurked like a bogeyman at the periphery of this story for the past year. It is the threatening body, nameless and faceless, of an armed and dangerous black intruder ...<br></p></blockquote> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-53158035e4b0da1677ed2cb0\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-03-04T07:26:50.359Z\">7.26am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440748142649024512\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Pistorius&amp;src=hash\">#Pistorius</a> enters high court in Pretoria with bodyguard holding arm and police shouting &quot;make way&quot; amid much pushing and shoving.</p>&mdash; David Smith (@SmithInAfrica) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica/statuses/440748142649024512\">March 4, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-53157f35e4b0984a90a9e0b1\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-03-04T07:23:57.619Z\">7.23am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Here are yesterday’s key events:</p><h2>Summary</h2><p><b>• A witness told the trial that she heard “bloodcurdling screams” on the night the Paralympian shot his girlfriend dead.</b></p><p><b>• The witness, Michelle Burger, told the court she heard two people - a man and a woman - shouting</b><b>, adding: </b><b>“The fear in that woman’s voice; you only fear like that if your life is threatened.”</b></p><p><b>• Burger said she heard four gunshots on the night in question.<br></b></p><p><b>• Pistorius pleaded not guilty to the murder and to firearms charges, telling the court he denied the allegations of murder “in the strongest terms” and believed an intruder had broken into his house and was in his bathroom when he fired.<br></b></p><p><b>• Pistorius said he approached the bathroom with a gun in an effort to protect Steenkamp and accused the prosecution of once again using “unsubstantiated allegations” to argue that he murdered Steenkamp.</b></p><p><b>• The Paralympian also accused the prosecution of trying to use inadmissible evidence for the “assassination of my character” and said that suggestions he deliberately killed Steenkamp “could not be further from the truth”.</b></p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-53157e2fe4b0da1677ed2caf\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-03-04T07:23:57.619Z\">7.23am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Good morning and welcome to our live coverage of the second day of the trial of Oscar Pistorius, who is accused of murdering his girlfriend, Reeva Steenkamp, on 14 February last year. Once again, our Africa correspondent, David Smith, will be in court D at the North Gauteng high court in Pretoria. You can follow his tweets <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SmithInAfrica\">here</a>. You can read his report of the first day’s events <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/mar/03/oscar-pistorius-reeva-steenkamp-murder-trial-opens\">here</a>.<br></p> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2014-03-04T07:35:34.363Z\">at 7.35am GMT</time></p> </div>","headline":"Oscar Pistorius trial - day two","trailText":"Full coverage of the trial of the South African athlete for the murder of his girlfriend, \nReeva Steenkamp, at his home in Pretoria on V