b disposal experts launched an investigation as the devices that bore \"all the hallmarks of Northern Ireland-related terrorism\".</p><p>An MoD spokeswoman said: \"We can confirm there is an ongoing incident at HMS Collingwood, the Royal Navy warfare school in Fareham, Hampshire,\" but that it would be inappropriate to make further comment.</p><p>HMS Collingwood is the headquarters of the navy's maritime warfare school, where training includes weapon engineering, diving, physical training, chemical, biological, radiation, nuclear and damage control, sea survival, seamanship and military skills.</p><p>A package was found in Aldershot, Hampshire, on Wednesday, while two packets were found on Tuesday at the armed forces careers office in Reading, Berkshire, and the army and RAF careers office in Chatham, Kent.</p><p>Although the devices were viable, they were crude and basic, making them unlikely to cause serious injury.</p><p>A Metropolitan police spokesperson said: \"We are aware of the claim of responsibility for the devices that were sent to army recruitment centres in England last week. The claim was received on Saturday 15 February by a Northern Irish media outlet using a recognised codeword. The claim was allegedly made on behalf of the 'IRA'.</p><p>\"The public is urged to remain vigilant and report anything suspicious to the anti-terrorist hotline 0800 789 321.\"</p>","headline":"Security alert at Hampshire naval base was false alarm","trailText":"Police cordon was set up due to reports of a suspicious package at HMS Collingwood, home of Royal Navy training centre","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/2/17/1392636680481/Police-tape-006.jpg","wordcount":"313","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2014-02-20T11:32:14Z"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2014/feb/17/suspicious-package-hms-collingwood-naval-base","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/uk-news/2014/feb/17/suspicious-package-hms-colli